They give the impression that Kushner was the one behind Flynn's infamous calls, but Kushner only directed Flynn to ask the Russian ambassador to delay or defeat a U.N. vote on Israeli settlements. If you didn't read carefully, you'd get the impression that the calls happened without Trump's involvement.

These anomalies are hard to explain. The media knows the implications of Trump directing Flynn's calls, but multiple supposedly independent media outlets are instead downplaying and misleading people about a key piece of information in scandal that could bring down the President of the United States.

If we want politicians who are accountable to us instead of a foreign power, we have to deter foreign influence in our elections. If that doesn't work, and a politician tries to help a foreign power get away with meddling in our elections on his or her behalf, then that politician must face consequences. Our media is failing us on both counts.




